{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a SecureField when you want behavior similar to a TextField, but you don’t want the user’s text to be visible. Typically, you use this for entering passwords and other sensitive information."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A SecureField uses a binding to a string value, and a closure that executes when the user commits their edits, such as by pressing the Return key. The field updates the bound string on every keystroke or other edit, so you can read its value at any time from another control, such as a Done button."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .center) {","    CSSecureField(password: viewStore.binding(","        get: {","            $0.pdfPassword","        },","        send: {","            Action.pdfPassword($0)","        }))"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The password is hidden."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"CSSecure_IsHidden"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The password is displayed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"CSSecure_Shown"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/cshub-test\/cssecurefield"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/cshub-test\/cssecurefield"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/cz.csas.app.cshub.test\/documentation\/CSHub-Test\/CSSecureField","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A control into which the user securely enters private text."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"CSSecureField","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"CSHub_Test"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/cz.csas.app.cshub.test\/d